s13 -- March 2024; Current iteration of Simpleton--don't blink for it will have changed.
 
This version is a set of Python files. 
It also uses MongoDB to store data.
The code, data structures, and process flow are highly volative.

Process order:
      
   1) processRawKB.py           -.- Builds starter MongoDb KB collection from started KB text file.
   2) processRawinflections.py  -.- Builds a MongoDB inflection collection from text file.
   3) processRawCorpus.py       -*- Builds 3 collections: taggedBoW, taggedCorpus, and untaggedCorpus from text files in Corpus folder.
   					Modify to process each file (book) one at a time...
   4) buildKB.py                -*- Build a KB from the starterKB and current corpus...~? Should be fun...
   *** Comprehension engine ***
        
          Predict the main idea
        1  Scan for unfamiliar words
        2  Scan and numbers paragraphs
          Predict genre or text type
          Identify the central idea
          Analyze text structure
          Identify key details
          Make inferences
        
   ?) rectifyKB.py              -?- Optional: Attemping to rectify BOW and KB, or add new to webWords (current focus)
   ?) accumulateKB.py           -?- Process and save semi-permanent "accumulated" universal KBs
   x) processInput.py           -- Process user input--chatbot

Utilities:
   commonUtils.py    -- Common functions
   
Configuration:
   commonConfig.py   -- Global variables

Sub-Folders:
   Corpus    -- Input docs
   data      -- Starter data and test input
   kb        -- Starter KB data



Previous verion:    
   
   checkPickles.py   -- Pickle checker
   simpSA.py         -- Rudimentary sentence analysis
   simpGA.py         -- Was supposed to be a rudimentary grammar analysis * Evolved into kbChecker.py
   kbChecker.py      -- Checks Simp, subject(s), and verbs against KB returns kbRes_Obj
   processOutput.py  -- Plan is to take output of processInput.py and attempt appropriate response
   scrapeWord.py     -- Scrape word definition from web
   addWebWords.py    -- Add new scrpaed words to webWords collection 
   checkWord.py      -- Checks if word exists in tagged corpus, tagged BOW, and KB
   kbChecker.py      -- Different method/form of simpGA.py   


   pickles   -- Aunt Bees pickle jar

